air** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/core/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/core/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/functional-spec.md](../forge/docs/functional-spec.md). |\n./docs/functional-spec.md:47:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` mirror of per-version metrics — `stats.json` (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information) produced by the harness, alongside the schema-validated `execution-metrics.json` each Forge run records.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:59:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:79:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/functional-spec.md:82:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n./docs/functional-spec.md:96:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:99:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/functional-spec.md:126:| `chunked-dynamic-access` | Issue | Forge split dynamic-access generation for this issue into class-aligned chunks because the uncovered class count exceeded the configured threshold. Normal project status controls whether Forge may claim the next chunk. |\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/JarUtils.java:61:                    // Convert path to FQCN: replace '/' with '.' and strip .class\n./docs/goals.md:35:state 